stylometry:
SUMPRODUCT is the products of two or more different numbers, added together.  
VLOOKUP acts similarly to a tax table.  It allows you to reference one cell, and put it in another cell.
SUMIF is a what if scenario that adds two parts together.  "if the problem = 0, then, if the product doesn't = 0, then"
IF similar to SUMIF, besides the addition.  If one scenario happens, this will occur. 

All of these excel functions help to save the user time, and makes the user work more effieciently if they know how to use these functions properly.
